.SH NAME
coa-tools-build - Compile binaries and generate native distribution packages (.deb, PKGBUILD)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcoa tools build [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
The 'build' command is the integrated packaging tool for the coa/oa ecosystem.
It orchestrates the full compilation of both the C-native engine (oa) and the Go-based orchestrator (coa), triggers the automatic generation of documentation and shell completions, and finally packages everything into native distribution formats like .deb (Debian/Ubuntu) or PKGBUILD (Arch Linux).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for build


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Compile the ecosystem and generate native packages
  coa tools build
.EE


